title: Non Coprime Sequences(Hard)
text: DefineF(n, m)to be the number of sequences of lengthnwhich satisfy:All elements of the sequence are positive divisors ofmFor any two adjacent elements, say p and q, there exists at least one prime which divides both of them.You are given two integers, n and m. Find the values ofF(1, m), F(2, m), ... F(n, m)modulo109+7InputThe only line of input contains two integers, n and m.Constraints0 < n ≤ 1050 < m ≤ 1018OutputPrint the values ofF(1, m), F(2, m) ... F(n, m)modulo109+7in a single line separated by space.ExampleInput:2 10Output:4 7
